    {
      "id": "PopularPost163396",
      "post_content": "I'd usually rather play [Putrid Raptor](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Putrid Raptor), but then again I play lots of Zombies. Still, though, Putrid Raptor can be dropped for ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol), instead of ![1](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=1&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) (good for a Grixis deck perhaps?), it's a 2/2 instead of being sacrificed, and the discard can wait until you're ready. Only advantage of this one is that it doesn't have to be a Zombie. You can't even reanimate this unless you have a creature in hand, and you can do that with the Raptor.  \n  \n@carnophage\\_4ever: You don't sacrifice another creature to it. You discard it. [Grave Pact](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grave Pact) won't trigger.",
      "posted_by": "Tynansdtm",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost163396\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_post\">I'd usually rather play <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Putrid Raptor\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Putrid Raptor\">Putrid Raptor</a>, but then again I play lots of Zombies. Still, though, Putrid Raptor can be dropped for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"3\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=3&amp;type=symbol\"/>, instead of <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"1\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=1&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> (good for a Grixis deck perhaps?), it's a 2/2 instead of being sacrificed, and the discard can wait until you're ready. Only advantage of this one is that it doesn't have to be a Zombie. You can't even reanimate this unless you have a creature in hand, and you can do that with the Raptor.<br/><br/>@carnophage_4ever: You don't sacrifice another creature to it. You discard it. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Grave Pact\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Grave Pact\">Grave Pact</a> won't trigger.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl08_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '163396'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy